  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Vascularized lymph node flap transfer (VLNT) was believed to be the treatment of choice for&#xD;
      moderate-to-severe lymphedema. Recent publications have supported the use of&#xD;
      supermicrosurgical lymphaticovenous anastomosis (LVA) for treating severe lymphedema. This&#xD;
      study hypothesizes whether LVA can be performed on post-VLNT patients seeking further&#xD;
      improvement.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
